<h2> Official Biographical Sketch </h2>
<p>
Hridesh Rajan is an Associate Professor of <a href="http://www.cs.iastate/edu">
Computer Science</a> at <a href="http://www.iastate.edu">
Iowa State University</a>, where he has been since August 2005.
He received his PhD in
<a href="http://www.cs.virginia.edu/">Computer Science</a>
from the <a href="http://www.virginia.edu">University of Virginia</a>
in 2005 under supervision of
<a href="http://www.cs.virginia.edu/~sullivan">Kevin Sullivan</a>.
He received his undergraduate degree from 
<a href="http://itbhu.ac.in">Institute of Technology</a>, 
Banaras Hindu University(IT-BHU) in 2000. 
Before his graduate studies at UVA, he 
worked for Lucent Technologies, India (Bell Labs, India)
as a Member of Technical Staff. 
Professor Rajan's research interests include
programming language design and implementation
and software engineering. 
Professor Rajan is a recepient of the National Science Foundation CAREER award in 2009
and LAS Award for Early Achievement in Research in 2010.
</p>
