<h2>Academic Background</h2>
<p></p>
<p>
My advisor at <a href="http://www.virginia.edu">University of Virginia</a> 
was <a href="http://www.cs.virginia.edu/~sullivan">Kevin Sullivan</a>, whose
advisor was <a href="http://www.cs.washington.edu/homes/notkin/">David Notkin</a>.
My <a href="http://www.csc.ncsu.edu/faculty/xie/sefamily.htm">academic genealogy</a>
goes all the way to <a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/EWD">Edsger Dijkstra.</a>
</p>

<p>
In prior life, I worked at <a href="http://www.bell-labs.com">Bell Labs</a> India,
the R&amp;D organization of <a href="http://www.lucent.com">Lucent Technologies</a>.
At the time, I was interested in bandwidth and power optimization issues in mobile
ad hoc & sensor networks as they scale up. I still keep up with these topics.
</p>

<h2>Personal</h2>

<p>
I come from a small town called Mokama in <a href="http://gov.bih.nic.in/Profile/history.htm">Bihar</a>, 
<a href="http://indiaimage.nic.in/">India</a>. I have had the pleasure to live within 
50ft from the river Ganga, a major river in India, for most of my childhood. 
If you are from Mokama, I will be glad to hear from you. Send me an e-mail and
we can share stories :-).
</p>

<p>
Beside computer science, I love
<a href="http://virginiasports.collegesports.com/sports/m-footbl/va-m-footbl-body.html">
